  , issueCommentBody =
      "You can already do this by using the `--fetch` options to `configure` from the top-level directory:\r\n\r\n```\r\n./configure --fetch coffee --fetch browserify --allow-fetch\r\nmake js-dist\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `--allow-fetch` is to let our `make` system configure everything in case you wanted to use a larger `make`.\r\n\r\nBut you do make a decent argument for us to make `coffee` and `browserify` non-optional fetches, since we are not validating other versions (and the implication is that newer versions don't work)."
